http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=12869243
For details on mass rebuild see https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_24_Mass_Rebuild

This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 24 development cycle. Changing version to '24'.
More information and reason for this action is here: https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_Program_Management/HouseKeeping/Fedora24#Rawhide_Rebase

Created attachment 1136976 Patch to fix the FTBFS
This package uses bools to initialize pointers. This is not allowed in c++14.
The patch in the attachment (against fedora git/master) should resolve this issue. Unless somebody objects, I'll apply this patch to rawhide and f24 in near future.
NB: This package's spec is carrying a lot of historic ballast and therefore could use a "brush-up". Also, the shape this package is in raises doubts on whether this package is still maintained in Fedora.
